==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Seven-thirties
<hw>Sev`en-thir"ties</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <def>A name
given to three several issues of United States Treasury notes, made
during the Civil War, in denominations of $50 and over, bearing interest
at the rate of seven and three tenths (thirty hundredths) per cent
annually. Within a few years they were all redeemed or funded.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Seventhly</ent>⟦br⟧
